                    <h4 class="panel-title">
                        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2">
                            What is IPFS?</a>
                    </h4>
                </div>
                <div id="collapse2" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <p>
                            IPFS is a peer-to-peer decentralized data distribution and storage protocol. Any computer
                            connected to the internet can participate as a peer in the IPFS network. If someone is
                            hosting a website on the IPFS network, then any client accessing this website becomes an
                            accessible host for other clients, too. The backbone of this website is a cluster of IPFS
                            nodes, which stores data permanently, immutable and distributed with a defined replication
                            factor. The benefit of this cluster is that any computer can extend this cluster, and
                            therefore one can build a large distributed and decentralized storage solution. The
                            underlying database holds meta-data of the files stored on IPFS. This means every
                            participant holds a copy of the database. If one node adds data, this message is immediately
                            published to other nodes, until it travels through the whole network.
                        </p>

