                    </h4>
                </div>
                <div id="collapse5" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        This website is part of the Storage UI API, so any (server-) node who is running the cluster also runs this website.
                        All nodes share the same database and the contents are distributed on all the nodes with a minimum replication factor
                        of 3.
                        This means, if you have your IPFS contents address (link) you have anytime access to your content.
                        In future you don't even need special tools to access an IPFS link. Mozilla Firefox for instance already built in the protocol by default.
                    </div>
